Author: designer#4893
Content:
Three major tragedies in life are poverty in old age, scars in middle age and, finally, success at too young age.

Who wouldn't welcome success? But I think you should be afraid. You can see a lot of people who succeed at a young age and fall apart before the golden age of life.

If one is already successful (=money) upon birth, the problem becomes more complicated. Without a special dream or ambition, it is probably an environment that is easy to ruin.

Author: designer#4893
Content:
smart-contract, automatically implemented without the help of the court, was a dream of Western civilization. this term was not designed by Vitalik, came out in the mid-1990s, the era of the Internet. But smart-contract is a beautiful story that is hard to reach.
 
the simple contract that humans make is much more complicated than the Go game in limited space. 

nevertheless, one of the lawyers' sites in the United States, spellbound by the excitedly of the beautiful story that the smart-contract platform be developed by teen genius programmer.

they said "In the future, lawyers need to be coded to survive, but whether they are quick to teach law to coders or whether it is fast for attorneys to learn coding," they argued.

Data quantification is one of the goals of modernity, but it is still rudimentary.

The figure of corporate value of a stock company, which many stakeholders are pushing for, is also a combination of meaningless conjectures. 

Before the smart-contract, all contexts about the contract must be clearly expressed in quantified language in order for the contract to be automatically implemented. It would take dozens of books to specify all the possibilities even if they were to sign a very simple contract.

People don't get fooled if you tell a story that's But if you go beyond people's imagination and tell perfectly beautiful stories, people are unexpectedly gullible.

It may be because people are locking themselves in their own fortresses that will keep their souls beautiful from the irrationality of reality.
